  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The erection of a roof extension, due to its size and siting and design, would detract from the character and appearance of the locally listed building. It would be highly visible from long front, side and rear views of the property and due to this, it would detract from the character and appearance of the Arlington Square Conservation Area to its detriment. This would conflict with of policies D1 (Overall Design), D3 (Site Planning), D4 (Designing in Context), D11 (Alterations and Extensions), D22 (New Development), D24 (Materials), D25 (Roof Extensions) and D42 (Building on the Local List) of Islington's Unitary Development Plan 2002, the Conservation Area Design Guidelines SPG (2002), Islington Urban Design Guide SPG (2006) and PPG15 (Planning and the Historic Environment)."
